# Dataset Rules

## MuscleActivationDataset
- Scan dataset_root for sequence dirs containing activations.npy + smplx_322.npy + semantic_label.txt
- Load muscle_names.json; assert len == N_muscles
- Filter sequences with T < min_T (default 30)
- Window sequences longer than max_T with stride = max_T // 2
- Return dict: {text: str, motion: Tensor[T,322], acts: Tensor[T,80], mask: BoolTensor[T], true_T: int}

## Label cleaning
    import re
    def clean_label(sample_id: str) -> str:
        s = re.sub(r'_clip\d+$', '', sample_id, flags=re.IGNORECASE)
        s = re.sub(r'_\d+$', '', s)
        return s.replace('_', ' ').strip().lower()

- Prefer semantic_label.txt IF not a numeric blob (>50% tokens parseable as float -> numeric)
- Fall back to clean_label(sample_id) for numeric blobs

## Version selector
- config.data.dataset_version (e.g. "v1"): load from dataset_root/v1/ if set
- Fall back to dataset_root/ with warning if versioned path missing

## Windowing note (for README)
- Same text label used for all windows of same sequence — intentional, not leakage
